children.text: Select the ID of the relevant business.
Select the ID of the catalog.
Enter the name of the product feed.
Replace Schedule: A full replace operation where items not present in the feed file will be removed, new items will be created and existing items will be updated.
Update Schedule:  Update existing items with the information delta provided or create new ones if not present.
URL: Enter the location of the product feed to fetch.
Interval: Select the interval at which the product feed gets fetched.

Hour: Enter the hour of the day to fetch the product feed, PDT during summer and PST during winter.  Note  If the Interval is hourly and Interval Count more than 0, the next upload will occur the Interval Count time after the upload.
Minute: Enter the minute of the hour to fetch the product feed.

Interval Count: Specify number of intervals between each upload, default is 1. For example, when Interval Count is 2 with Interval set to daily, feed will we uploaded every two days at the given time.
Username: Enter the username needed to access the url.
Enter the two letter country code where the products can be sold.
Enter the default currency used by provided feed if the currency is not specified in the feed file.

When true, this will remove products from a catalog that are no longer present in a feed. When false, uploading a product feed is additive and products will remain in the catalog even if they are removed from a feed. This field cannot be disabled once enabled.
Select the character encoding used by the provided feed.
Select the type of the feed. Decides type of catalog item this feed will create.
Enter the name of the product feed.
Select the ingestion source type to decide type of feed.
Select the sub type of items to be uploaded by this feed.
Video Game Consoles and Video Games

Used to split an original feed into multiple new feeds, this denotes the original feed's ID. Setting this field ensures that items from an original field can be migrated to a new one, without the need of deletion. This field is generally used when splitting a large feed into multiple smaller feeds.
You have a large feed called Feed A and want to split it.The items from feed A have been moved to feed B.
You create a new feed called Feed B and specify Feed A's ID under Migrated From Feed ID.
You upload Feed B's catalog information, including the products you want to add to Feed B.
Going forward, you do not need to specify those items in Feed A and they can be removed from feed A.
Select whether or not there will be quotes around each field, only for TSV feeds.
Add a list of rules applied to feed uploads using a JSON-encoded string.
Add any selected override fields of the feed.
Retrieves the details of a product feed by its ID.

<style>
@media print {
  html, body {
    overflow-x: visible;
  }
}
#tally-widget-button {
  position: fixed !important;
  background-color: #FFFFFF;
  display: none;
  visibility: visible !important;
  opacity: 1 !important;
  color: #0C121D;
  border: 2px solid #0C121D;
  border-radius: 4px;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-family: 'Inter';
  text-align: center;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  cursor: pointer;
  z-index: 999999 !important;
  -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
  outline: none;
  touch-action: manipulation;
  pointer-events: auto;
  transform: translate3d(0, 0, 0);
}
.button-text {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-right: 8px;
}
.button-text::before {
  content: attr(data-text);
}
#tally-widget-popup {
  position: fixed;
  background-color: white;
  display: none;
  border-radius: 12px;
  box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
  z-index: 999999;
  overflow: hidden;
  border: 0px solid #0C121D;
  padding-top: 30px;
}
#tally-widget-close {
  position: absolute;
  top: 10px;
  right: 10px;
  background: none;
  border: none;
  font-size: 36px;
  font-weight: bold;
  padding: 8px;
  cursor: pointer;
  color: #0C121D;
}

  .ab-plugin-wrapper .ab-link-block-item .ab-link {
    color: #7302D5 !important;
    font-family: 'Inter' !important;
  }

  .dark .ab-plugin-wrapper .ab-link-block-item .ab-link {
    color: #F6F6F6 !important;
  }
  
  #main-column > div > div > div.flex.flex-1.w-full.justify-center.pb-0 > div > div.flex.items-center.pl-0.pr-2.mb-5.xl\:-mt-1\.5 > div > div > div > div:nth-child(1) > div.flex.pr-2.text-gray-500.items-center {
    color: #7302D5 !important;
  }

  a.ab-tree-navigation-link-active span {
    color: #7302D5 !important;
  }

  .ab-public-space-links-wrap .ab-public-space-link:first-of-type {
    border-color: #7302D5 !important;
  }

  .ab-toc-item-active a{
    color: #7302D5 !important;
  }

  #main-column .text-ab-blue-500 span {
    color: #7302D5 !important;
  }
  
  #main-column .text-ab-blue-500 {
    text-decoration-color: #7302D5 !important;
  }
  .ab-nav-left:hover > svg,
  .ab-nav-left:hover .text-gray-300,
  .ab-nav-left:hover .ab-nav-left-text {
     color: #7302D5 !important;
     stroke: #7302D5 !important;
  }
  .ab-nav-right:hover > svg,
  .ab-nav-right:hover .text-gray-300,
  .ab-nav-right:hover .ab-nav-right-text {
     color: #7302D5 !important;
     stroke: #7302D5 !important;
  }
  
#tally-inline-popup {
  position: fixed;
  display: none;
  z-index: 999999;
  width: min(420px, 90vw);
  height: min(550px, 80vh);
  background: #fff;
  color: #0c121d;
  border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  border-radius: 12px;
  box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(0,0,0,0.22), 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
  overflow: hidden;
  padding: 5px;
}

#tally-inline-popup iframe {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  border: 0;
  display: block;
  border-radius: 8px;
}

#tally-inline-popup .tip-close {
  position: absolute;
  top: 6px;
  right: 8px;
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  line-height: 28px;
  font-size: 22px;
  text-align: center;
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
  border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  border-radius: 8px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

#main-column a[data-form-url],
#main-column a[data-tally-url] {
  color: #7302D5 !important;
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 2px;
  text-decoration-thickness: 1.5px;
  font-weight: 600;
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  #tally-inline-popup {
    width: min(360px, 94vw);
    height: min(500px, 80vh);
  }
}

#main-column .ab-cta-button a.ab-cta-button {
  background-color: #7302D5;
}

/* Titles in purple */
.ab-link-blocks-wrapper .ab-link-block-item.ab-docs-card-mode .ab-link-block-content-wrap .font-bold {
  color: #7302D5 !important;
}

.ab-tree-navigation-link-active span {
    color: #7302D5 !important;
}

</style>
